reviews.review_text: the fall of 1970 Alot of great music was going down in Grateful Dead land at this time.American beauty was fresh and i remember i was in high school but for some unknown reason we found ourselves eating little orange barrels and listening to the band just melt in our minds,this recording was 1 of those tapes that gotfrequent play in my nak.. this era of grateful deadness is what i cut my teeth on and as time went on,we went on.

Finally, a recording that does this show justice! I've reviewed this show before, but been unable to enjoy it due to crappy recordings. At the time of this review, there IS a more recent post, but it's nowhere near as good. A lot was done on this to make it sound good, and it was worth it. The set list is tricky and the jams are flowing and intense. The playing is great, in a way I couldn't hear on previous copies. So far, my favorite of the '70 shows.
